s=b.jE("What Makes T-LAB Different",B.QJ)
r=A.O(A.a([b.Vq("An elected Planning Team manages weekly meetings. A Finance Team runs the Goin economy. A Material Team oversees tools and resources. Children hold real authority \u2014 and develop real responsibility.",B.QN,B.R,"Children Run It"),B.S,b.ais("assets/Goine.png","The Goin is T-LAB's internal currency. Children earn Goins for making and sharing, spend them on materials, and negotiate the value of their finished projects with peers. Economics \u2014 lived, not taught.",B.as,"A Real Economy"),B.S,b.Vq("No assigned tasks. No required topics. Every child chooses what to make, plans it, builds it, fails, iterates, and presents it on a Sharing schedule. The facilitator supports \u2014 but never directs.",B.QK,B.rR,"Every Project Is Theirs")],a2),B.k,B.h,B.f)
q=b.jE("What We Offer",B.Qt)
p=A.O(A.a([b.ts("A T-LAB layout tailored to your room, your children, and your community. Six functional zones \u2014 Workstations, Material Storage, Planning Board, T-LAB Bank, Sharing Desk, and Meeting Circle \u2014 each designed for a specific purpose.",B.R1,"Space Design"),B.ai,b.ts("A curated kit across five domains: Electricity & Electronics, Mechanics, Soft Cutting (craft and art), Hard Cutting (wood and fabrication), and General Science (Chem/Bio). Includes storage for scrap materials.",B.kv,"Materials & Tools"),B.ai,b.ts("Every system documented for your facilitator \u2014 the Goin economy, governance and elections, the planning board, Sharing protocol, and the facilitation approach. Your lab's complete operating guide.",B.QT,"The T-LAB Handbook"),B.ai,b.ts("A detailed orientation on T-LAB's facilitation approach \u2014 how to observe, ask generative questions, and hold space without instructing. Ongoing mentorship and reflection support throughout the first year.",B.QW,"Facilitator Orientation & Mentorship"),B.ai,b.ts("Regular onsite visits throughout the year, remote support between visits, facilitator reflection sessions, and connection to the T-LAB network across India. The goal: a lab that runs itself.",B.Rq,a0),B.ai,b.ts("Every child in your T-LAB joins the MiniGuru network \u2014 documenting their projects, sharing with children in other T-LAB schools and STEAM spaces, and connecting with a community of young makers across India.",B.QX,"MiniGuru Community Access")],a2),B.k,B.h,B.f)
