a4=A.A(a0,A.O(A.a([A.a_(A.a([A.av(A.O(A.a([A.d("A Tinkering Corner for Your Child \u2014 At Home",a0,a0,a0,a0,a0,A.a3().$4$color$fontSize$fontWeight$height(B.c,20,B.q,1.3),a0,a0,a0),B.N,A.d("Designed around their specific curiosity.\nNot a kit. Not a toy corner. A real making space.",a0,a0,a0,a0,a0,A.a3().$4$color$fontSize$fontWeight$height(A.y(242,B.c.gi()>>>16&255,B.c.gi()>>>8&255,B.c.gi()&255),14,B.H,1.4),a0,a0,a0)],a5),B.r,B.h,B.f),1),B.b1,B.a9P],a5),B.k,B.h,B.f,a0),B.S,A.d("Every child has something they are quietly drawn to \u2014 circuits and electricity, clay and sculpture, wood and construction, science and experiment. Most homes have nowhere for that curiosity to go. A tinkering corner gives it a place. We help you design the right space, choose the right materials, and set it up so that your child is invited to make \u2014 and keeps coming back.",a0,a0,a0,a0,a0,A.a3().$3$color$fontSize$height(A.y(217,B.c.gi()>>>16&255,B.c.gi()>>>8&255,B.c.gi()&255),13,1.6),a0,a0,a0)],a5),B.r,B.h,B.f),B.i,a0,a0,new A.D(a0,a0,a0,a4,a0,B.Up,B.l),a0,a0,B.n9,B.co,a0,a0,a0)
s=a.jE("Why a Dedicated Space?",B.uF)
r=A.O(A.a([a.Nq(B.uS,"A Space Signals Permission","When a child has their own corner \u2014 their own tools, their own materials, their own space \u2014 it signals something important: this is real. Your making matters. That signal changes how they engage."),B.ai,a.Nq(B.QR,"Materials Invite Ideas","The right materials in view spark projects that wouldn't otherwise arrive. A child who can see wire, clay, cardboard, and small motors is already planning something."),B.ai,a.Nq(B.uT,"Continuity Builds Depth","The best making happens over multiple sessions \u2014 returning to a project, rebuilding after failure, trying a different approach. A permanent corner makes this possible in a way that a one-off kit or activity never can.")],a5),B.k,B.h,B.f)
q=a.jE("How It Works",B.ur)
p=a.Xt("01",B.d4,"A Conversation \u2014 With Your Child","We begin with a short call with you and your child together. What is your child curious about? What do they like to make, take apart, or experiment with? What space is available at home? The child's voice shapes everything that follows.","The corner must belong to your child, not to the parent's idea of what their child should be interested in. This first conversation ensures it does.")
o=a.Lz("02",B.M8,"Your Space & Materials Plan","Based on the conversation, we design a simple layout for the available space \u2014 even a corner of a room or a single dedicated shelf works \u2014 and a curated materials list matched to your child's interests. Not a generic kit. A specific starter collection for specific ideas.")
n=a.Lz("03",B.hU,"Setting Up","Materials arrive with a setup guide, age-appropriate safety notes for parents, and a first-project suggestion to help the corner come alive immediately. For families in Bhopal, Ujjain, Pune, or nearby cities, we offer an optional in-person setup session.")
m=a.Lz("04",B.c8,"Staying Connected","Periodic check-in calls where your child shares what they have made, gets suggestions for what to try next, and connects with the MiniGuru community of young makers. We stay involved for as long as it is useful.")
